Mark IV Industries Inc &lt;IV>, whichhas said it may consider a bid to seek control of Baird Corp,said Baird has not agreed to hold off on any defensive measureswithout giving Mark IV at least 24 hours notice.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,Mark IV corrected a statement it made yesterday in another SECfiling in which it listed several agreements reached withBaird, including that Baird would not take any anti-takeoversteps without providing at least 24 hours notice.    Mark IV said it was later told by Baird that Baird hadgiven no such assurance. Reuter&#3;